text: Input/Output Data The input/output data is the type of data an agent expects and delivers. Produced types are dependent on input type and the APL code. The agent consumes byte arrays and any UDR type selected from the UDR Types list. MIM The agent does not publish or access any additional MIM parameters. However, MIM parameters and values/Agent Message events/Debug events can be produced/accessed/dispatched through APL. For further information about available functions, see the section MIM Related Functions in the APL Reference Guide .
